    "like_dislike_summary": {
      "pos_sentences": [
        "This course will be very helpful for my competitive exams, so I chose it.",
        "The placement cell and job opportunities are quite good, but its not too efficient. It needs some improvements. There is an alumni and entrepreneur cell in this college.",
        "We have to pay half of the fee in the first semester and the remaining amount in the second semester.",
        "Students cannot bring their cell phones to college. It is strictly prohibited and punishable. This policy allows faculties to utilize the wifi facilities. The computer labs are well-maintained and up to date. During a visit to the food and nutrition department lab, I noticed that it is also well-maintained.",
        "6 June is the application date. Reservation benefits are available. You can mostly see the AO of the college; he will tell you about the admission process, thats all."
      ],
      "neg_sentences": [
        "The placement cell and job opportunities at this college are fewer than at other colleges. They have tied up with very few companies. This year, there is no placement cell due to the pandemic period.",
        "Scholarship is given, but it is provided too late for us to use. Similarly, a loan is offered, but the students are unable to obtain it. The main issue is that the fees amount is low, making it impossible for our college to provide a loan for this amount.",
        "There are sports, wifi, library, canteen, and laboratory facilities. However, the library is not big. On the positive side, this college conducts a lot of functions. On the negative side, mobile phones, jeans, and leggings are not allowed"
      ]
    },
